2\pi
f(x)
f(x) = \begin{cases} \frac{\pi}{4}-\frac{x}{2} & x\in [0,\pi] \\ -\frac{3\pi}{4}+\frac{x}{2}, & x\in(\pi,2\pi) \end{cases}
f(2\pi-x) = \begin{cases} \frac{\pi}{4}-\frac{2\pi-x}{2} & x\in [\pi,2\pi] \\ -\frac{3\pi}{4}+\frac{2\pi-x}{2}, & x\in (0,\pi) \end{cases}
 = \begin{cases} \frac{-3\pi}{4}+\frac{x}{2} & x\in [\pi,2\pi] \\ +\frac{1\pi}{4}-\frac{x}{2}, & x\in (0,\pi) \end{cases}
f(2\pi-x)=f(x)\text{   (1)}
